posts.name: Emre
posts.cooked: I didn’t find your namedcommands in robot.java. You didn’t update the code? Or initialized somewhere else? You should register your commands before any auto and after subsystem initializations. Follow the docs. https://pathplanner.dev/pplib-named-commands.html
Our namedcommands are under the registercommands() method in AutoLogic.java and the issue doesn’t seem to be because of a lack of add requirements as there are command factories that have it build in

posts.name: icemannie
posts.cooked: NamedCommands.registerCommand(“autoAlign”, autoAlignmentCommand()); has PathPlanner content. Try without it as a test.

I already did that, and the paths work just fine.  I believe the issue may be code differences between two laptops as the laptop I worked on is not the one that was used for tests no so the code may need to be pushed in the second laptop?and again the issue is with NamedCommands.registerCommand intake

posts.name: icemannie
posts.cooked: So in registerCommands() you commented out both NamedCommands.registerCommand(“autoAlign”, autoAlignmentCommand());and you still get Named Command errors;? NamedCommands has other methods like .hasCommand you can try for test also.
We have fixed the issue by using as proxy onto the registered commands. However, the robot goes to the station, intakes but then just stops doing anything after that
